{
  "stem": "833.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You cannot replace a great musical line-- what it does to you-- by anything else.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Therefore, it is a communication that is irreplaceable.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And people forget that, and people who do not-- are not being taught early in life that this great communication is one side of life, which must also take part in the daily life or in-- in the natural, everyday life.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That this is not something special which you do on certain occasions, but it is part of-- of the-- the need for something, which nothing else can fill but the great-- the great expressions of music.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so if you do-- to be able to do something which expresses their-- their inner-- inner emotional-- like, it's difficult to say these words, because this-- otherwise, we wouldn't need music.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That this need is an innate one in the human race, regardless where it comes from.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And that told me to-- to write music and to make those music instruments with my-- there were some extraordinary people there.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You see, first of all, we had two or three first-rate music instrument makers in-- as-- as one of the prisoners from Munich.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They couldn't do-- of course, they didn't have the right tools.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they could make some things that sounded like music.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Mostly string instruments, you know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The cases where you put the string on top of it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there was-- didn't you read in the book?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, I see.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, I saw one of those SS men very soon who was shouting like mad, but was never doing anything mad-- anything bad.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And one day, I thought, this is-- must be a Communist spy or something like this.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
